	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Fairfield Con.</placeName> <date>July 13. 1854</date>.</p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#47;Have the kindness to send<lb/> me the <date>July</date> Number of the Occident to this place&#44; whether I have<lb/> removed with the views<add>&#63;</add> of rusticating for some time.&#8212;  May I<lb/> also trouble you with the following commission&#44; as I know no one<lb/> in your place&#44; whom I could address for that purpose.  Since <persName>Dr<lb/> Raphall</persName> has begun publishing his Postbiblical history of the Jews<lb/> in the <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia Sunday Dispatch</hi>&#44; I have been a sub&#45;<lb/>scriber to the paper.  Now&#44; my copy being sent to <placeName>Charleston</placeName>&#44; I<lb/> am interrupted in the perusal of the Drs history&#44; and would&#44; therefore<lb/> most respectfully beg you&#44; to buy the numbers of <del><date>July</date></del> <date>June 18</date>&#44; <date>June 25</date>&#44;<lb/> <date>July 2</date>&#44; <date>July 9</date> &#38; <date>July 16</date> and send them to me with the Occident.<lb/>  My <date>August</date> number of the Occident you will be kind enough<lb/> to send me&#44; directed to the care of <persName>Mrs S. Mayer</persName>&#44; <placeName>412 Grand<lb/> Str. N. York</placeName>&#44; whither&#44; if you will oblige me still more&#44; you<lb/> might send me also <del>from</del> the continuations of the Sunday Dis&#45;<lb/>patch from <date>July 23</date> to <date>Aug 20</date>.&#44; the time of my absence from <placeName>Ch.</placeName><lb/> In passing through <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; I shall take pleasure in re&#45;<lb/>funding you all outlays.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Ever ready to serve you in return&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Your&#44; most friendly</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName></p>
				<p>care of <persName>Mr John A Philips</persName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Fairfield&#44; Con.</placeName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
